                    <li>
                        <h5>CSS - Cascading StyleSheet</h5>
                        <div>
                            <p>
                                After arranging the blocks of the web page dont forget you will have to paint  it and add
                                some finishing touches and <span class="extra">CSS</span> is the right tool for that
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                CSS can be added to html tags in three different ways thats is the
                                <ul style="padding-left: 16px;">
                                    <li>inline styling</li>
                                    <li>internal styling</li>
                                    <li>external styling</li>
                                </ul>
                            </p>
                            <div class="styleblock">
                                <div class="codeblocks">
                                    <pre class="codeblock"><code>"""inline method"""

&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;

&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;div style="color: white;"&gt;

    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;</code></pre>
                                </div>
                                
                                <div class="codeblocks">
                                    <pre class="codeblock"><code>"""internal method"""

&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;style&gt;
        .container{
            color: white;
        }
    &lt;/style&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;div class="container"&gt;

    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;</code></pre>
                                </div>
                                <div class="codeblocks">                                
                                    <pre class="codeblock"><code>"""external method"""

&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;link href="../location/file.css" &gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
    &lt;div class="container"&gt;

    &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;</code></pre>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <p>
                                but the preferred method is the external method which allows you to create a different css file in a different folder to write all your styles and just reference the file in your html file using the <span class="extra">link tag</span> eg.
                                you have a working folder in vscode with the project directory looking like this
                            </p>
                            <div class="style-example">
                                <div class="eg-inner">
                                    <div class="codeblocks">
                                        <pre class="codeblock"><code>
"""app challenge folder"""

    &#8964; assets
        &#8964; css
            style.css
        &#8964; js
            index.js
        &#8964; img
            user.png
    &#8964; views
        dashboard.ejs
    main.js
                                        </code></pre>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="codeblocks">
                                        <pre class="codeblock"><code>
"""dashboard.ejs"""

    &lt;html&gt;
    &lt;head&gt;
    &lt;link href="/css/style.css" &gt;
    &lt;/head&gt;
    &lt;body&gt;
        &lt;div class="container"&gt;
            &lt;div class="redbox"&gt;
                
            &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/body&gt;
    &lt;/html&gt;
                                        </code></pre>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="codeblocks">
                                        <pre class="codeblock"><code>
"""style.css"""

    .container{
        color: white;
        display: inline-block;
        background-color: black;
    }
    .container .redbox{
        width: 250px;
        height: 500px;
        background-color: red;
    }
                                        </code></pre>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <p>
                                There is a rule in using <span class="extra">internal styling</span> or <span class="extra">external styling</span> which is 
                                you need a <span class="extra">selector</span> to style a <span class="extra">tag</span> the selector can be either
                                <ul style="padding-left: 16px;">
                                    <li>tag name</li>
                                    <li>tag's class</li>
                                    <li>tag's id</li>
                                </ul>
                                but preferrably the class or tagname and a property with its value like this
                                <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; width: 50%; margin: 8px auto; ">
                                    <img width="512" height="auto" src="/img/learning/pic2.png" alt="">
                                </div>
                            </p>
                            <div class="style-example">
                                <div class="eg-inner">
                                    <div class="codeblocks">
                                        <pre class="codeblock"><code>
"""tag name selector"""

div{
    color: white;
    display: inline-block;
    background-color: black;
}
div .redbox{
    width: 250px;
    height: 500px;
    background-color: red;
}
                                        </code></pre>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="codeblocks">
                                        <pre class="codeblock"><code>
"""class selector"""

.container{
    color: white;
    display: inline-block;
    background-color: black;
}
.container .redbox{
    width: 250px;
    height: 500px;
    background-color: red;
}
                                        </code></pre>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="codeblocks">
                                        <pre class="codeblock"><code>
"""id selector"""

    #container{
        color: white;
        display: inline-block;
        background-color: black;
    }
    #container .redbox{
        width: 250px;
        height: 500px;
        background-color: red;
    }
                                        </code></pre>
